'''''Neoserica nyassica''''' is a species of [[beetle]] of the family [[Scarabaeidae]].<ref>[https://www.biolib.cz/en/taxon/id1674580/ BioLib]</ref> It is found in [[Malawi]].<ref name=":1">{{cite web |last= Schoolmeesters|first= P.|date= 2025|title= ''Neoserica (Neoserica) nyassica'' at Catalogue of Life|url=https://www.catalogueoflife.org/data/taxon/46TH5|website= World Scarabaeidae Database (version 2025-10-07). In O. Bánki, Y. Roskov, M. Döring, G. Ower, D. R. Hernández Robles, C. A. Plata Corredor, T. Stjernegaard Jeppesen, A. Örn, T. Pape, D. Hobern, S. Garnett, H. Little, R. E. DeWalt, J. Miller, T. Orrell, & R. Aalbu, Catalogue of Life (2026-01-16).|location= Amsterdam, Netherlands|publisher= Catalogue of Life Foundation|access-date=February 6, 2026}}</ref><ref name=":2" />

==Description==
Adults reach a length of about 6.5-7 mm. They are somewhat elongate-oval, dull and reddish yellowish-brown with a opalescent luster. The [[pronotum]] is almost straight laterally with distinct marginal [[setae]], also anteriorly. The posterior corners are rounded. The scutellum is narrow, the apex slightly rounded, with irregular punctures beside it. The narrow, slightly convex intervals are widely punctate and the marginal setae are dense and there are very faint, yellow setae laterally.<ref name=":2">{{cite journal|last1=Brenske|first1=E.|date= 1901|title= Die Serica-Arten der Erde. V.|url=https://www.zobodat.at/pdf/Berliner-Ent-Zeitschrift_46_0431-0462.pdf|journal=Berliner Entomologische Zeitschrift|volume= 46|issue=4|publisher= |pages= 431-462|doi= |access-date= February 6, 2026}} {{pd-notice}}</ref>
